# Final Operational Security & Configuration

This plan focuses on finalizing the production-readiness of the ICS Command Center by securing sensitive credentials and establishing a permanent audit trail for all critical administrative operations.

## User Review Required

> [!CAUTION]
> Hardcoded credentials will be removed from `server.js` and moved to a `.env` file. The server will require this file to start correctly in production.
> We will add an `audit_logs` table to the database. This will record specific details (who, what, when, IP) for watchlist and personnel changes.

## Proposed Changes

### [Backend] Configuration & Security

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-backend/server.js)
- Install and configure `dotenv`.
- Replace hardcoded `JWT_SECRET` and `PG_PASSWORD` with `process.env` references.
- Implement an `auditLog(userId, action, details)` helper function.
- Integrate audit logging into `POST/DELETE /api/watchlist` and `POST /api/users`.

#### [MODIFY] [schema.sql](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-backend/schema.sql)
- **[NEW TABLE]** `audit_logs`:
  - `id`, `user_id` (FK), `action`, `details`, `ip_address`, `created_at`.

